{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#3044: support isShallow",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:28:03.754941+00:00",
  "text": "support isShallow\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\r\nThe reactivity package lacks a way to determine the shallow type, so add an ```isShallow``` method like what ```isReadonly``` do.\r\n\r\nI want to use ```isShallow``` in my project to judge if a reactive is of type shallow.\r\n\r\n### What does the proposed API look like?\r\n```javascript\r\nimport { isShallow, shallowReactive } from 'vue'\r\nconst foo = shallowReactive({ test: 1 })\r\nif (isShallow(foo)) {\r\n  // ... do something\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request",
    "scope: reactivity"
  ],
